,Not Recommended,412880,20314257,"Posted: 4 January, 2016",all,Drummerkid51,"*UPDATE*Okay, so my original impression of this game was extremely positive. Price was low, drifting was actually super fun, and it was a fresh idea. Each update brought something new to the game, and I was genuinely enjoying my time with it. After a few months, they started messing with the handling. This is where it went downhill, in my opinion. At first the handling felt like it had some weight to it, and the controls were smooth. Now it feels like you're driving a piece of paper. Trying to hold a line is insanely aggravating, and turning feels extremely touchy. There's a nice bug where you'll barely tap the brakes and your car goes spinning like crazy. Also, it seems like it's damn near impossible to even go in a straight line anymore, so you're constantly fighting with the touchy steering. I'm sure some people still find this game enjoyable, but for me, that ended when they started messing with the handling. I can't play for more than a few minutes without getting annoyed. It's a bit disappointing really. I had high hopes for this game in the beginning, but unfortunately now I can't recommend it, even for $5.ORIGINAL REVIEWFinally a decent attempt at a drifting game. For $7, it's worth it. Even with only an hour into it, it's been super fun. It definitely has its flaws, as will any new game, but hopefully the developers will continue to work on this because it has potential to be awesome.Wish list:- More vehicles- More exterior customization (wheels, headlights, bumpers, skirts, wings, hoods, etc)- Driver (just a moving steering wheel in an empty seat makes the cockpit view lose immersion)- Better sound (car sounds and music come in and out constantly - had to mute the music for now)- Better control over throttle (in auto shifting, throttle response is laggy)- Better collision affects - maybe add an option to toggle collision with other players- Optimization for higher resolutions - playing in 1440p and have a weird box- Move the point indicator to a different position - definitely gets in the way all the time- The option to host a server and options/rules for that server- Customizable speedo and tach (colors, size, position)A big list, yes, but these are things I would definitely like to see out of a game with potential. I would recommend taking a lot of influence from NFS Underground 2 in regards to customization."
